@startuml CurrentPrototype
title Current Prototype Architecture (v0.1.0)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor User

package "Frontend (nginx)" {
    rectangle "React SPA\n+ ErrorBoundary" as UI
}

package "Backend Services" {
    rectangle "REST API\n(FastAPI)" as API
    database "PostgreSQL\n(indexed)" as DB
    rectangle "NATS\nJetStream" as NATS
    rectangle "Profiling\nScheduler" as Profiler
}

package "Worker" {
    rectangle "Job Worker\n(Python, async)" as JobWorker
}

package "Execution" {
    rectangle "Docker\nContainers" as Docker
    folder "Checkpoints" as Checkpoints
    folder "Run logs" as Logs
}

' Interactions
User --> UI : submit/stop/resume
UI --> API : HTTP (CORS-gated)
API --> DB : connection pool\n(psycopg-pool)
API --> NATS : publish events
NATS --> JobWorker : subscribe\n(ack/nak)
NATS --> Profiler : profiling_complete
Profiler --> DB : record results
Profiler --> NATS : re-schedule job
JobWorker --> Docker : run containers
JobWorker --> DB : progress updates
Docker --> Checkpoints : save/load
Docker --> Logs : stdout capture

note right of API
    • Job CRUD + pagination
    • Atomic stop/resume (no TOCTOU)
    • Image name validation
    • Path traversal protection
    • Health check (DB + NATS)
    • Credential masking in logs
    • DB indexes + CHECK constraint
end note

note right of JobWorker
    • Concurrent job execution
    • Event-driven (3 NATS consumers)
    • Async subprocess (non-blocking)
    • Duplicate job dedup
    • Graceful shutdown (SIGTERM/SIGINT)
    • Job timeout (configurable, default 24h)
    • NATS ack/nak with retry
    • State reconciliation on startup

    → Evolves to: Scheduler + K8s Actuator
end note

note right of Docker
    • Signal handling (SIGTERM → checkpoint)
    • Resumable execution
    • Profiling isolation (separate ckpt dir)
    • Resource limits via Compose

    → Evolves to: K8s Jobs / Pods
    → Docker CLI → Kubernetes API
end note

note right of Checkpoints
    → Evolves to: S3 (distributed storage)
end note

@enduml
